President Obama has declared a major disaster in the District of Columbia and has ordered Federal aid to help with recovery efforts following an earthquake that occurred between August 23-28, 2011. Federal funding will be available to the District of Columbia and certain nonprofit organizations for emergency work, facility repairs, and hazard mitigation measures. The Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) has appointed Kim R. Kadesch as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.